            <abstract xml:lang="en">
              <p>Hate speech detection is a challenging task of natural language processing. Recently, some works have focused on the use of multiword expressions for hate speech detection. In this paper, we propose to use an auxiliary task to improve hate speech detection: multiword expression identification. Our proposed system, based on multi-task with self-attention, outperforms an MWE-based features state-of-the-art system on four hate speech corpora.</p>
